 dropped but the stronger i-m-stronger uses). ~22 knobs; separate values for 2P-normal / 4P-normal /
 terminal — but 4P is the high-EV surface (2P config is identical across the whole public field).

 The missing piece: a LOW-NOISE evaluator (root cause of "no progress")

 Past evals were noise-dominated (n=28, ±18% CI, seat-biased) → we optimized noise. Fix it:
 - Gauntlet: comet_reaper + strong public bots (the-producer-v2, i-m-stronger, floor-matched, 1266-elo)
   - self, by explicit path (engine source is byte-identical → safe in-process in arena.py).
 - Seat-rotated 4P (focal through all 4 seats) + 2P; n ≥ 150–200 games/candidate → ~±5% CI.
 - Reuse arena.py run_4p_tournament (seat-rotation built in) + seat-fair eval worker. Parallel across cores.

 Optimizer: Optuna

 A Python framework that proposes configs (TPE/CMA-ES samplers), scores them on the gauntlet, prunes bad
 trials, and stores every trial in a queryable DB + dashboard. It IS our systematic tuner (vs ad-hoc
 sweeps). MLFlow is only a tracker (optional), not an optimizer — not needed.

