 Deducing edges beyond the 20 knobs (parallel diagnostic)

 If optimal config still falls short of 1500, the residual = structural edges the knobs can't express.
 To find them: policy-diff comet_reaper against the top private teams' replay states (we have their
 moves in the prize-zone data) — where does our planner's move differ from theirs? Check the family's 4
 known structural gaps for behavioral evidence: (a) single fleet size vs partial commits, (b) no
 opponent-reaction, (c) no own-turn search/lookahead, (d) shallow 4P coalition play. This tells us what to
 build after tuning saturates.

 Honest EV

 4P-config tuning is the highest-probability lever and we know the exact knobs the stronger bots use —
 but not guaranteed to reach 1500 (the engine is shared; top teams may have structural edges). We
 validate on the gauntlet before submitting, so the downside is only local compute.

 Verification

 arena.py --mode 4p seat-rotated + 2P, candidate vs the gauntlet, n≥200; report avg placement + 95% CI.
 Submittable only if it beats comet_reaper outside the CI on both 2P win% and 4P placement.


